<dl id="n40043c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40043c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40043c"> 43(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tempt / accuse / punish )</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the book of Enoch Satan is represented as the ruler of a rival kingdom of evil, but here are also mentioned Satans, who are distinguished from the fallen angels and who have a threefold function, to tempt, to accuse and to punish. <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
